In SABC1's prime-time soapie Skeem Saam, he plays Zamokuhle Seakamela, better known as Kwaito, who at some point was embroiled in a love triangle, but in real life Clement Maosa is expecting his first child. The 31-year-old actor proposed to his girlfriend Kemo Manyoga during his intimate birthday dinner celebration last year. He has constantly shared happy snaps of himself with his fiance on social media and now they are expecting a bundle of joy together. The elated star took to his Instagram account to share the good news with his followers. He shared a picture of his lady's baby bump and captioned it: "If be fruitful and multiply was a person". Dala ngi Lindile, Yes I Do, Ngiyavuma I.... ?? (If be fruitful and multiply was a person...??) #WCW ?? : @tendai_mhlanga A post shared by  Clementmaosa (@clementmaosa) on Sep 10, 2019 at 11:48pm PDT  